Millie Hi,



I'm going to need some more tangible information to cross-check this with
the bank. For example:



- Is there any kind of transaction identifier? Dates, amounts, etc.

- Which bank rejected this: the correspondent bank? The final destination
bank? Someone else along the chain?

- What was the formal rejection response?



Given that the first rejection was based on missing details of a
correspondent bank, which were subsequently supplied, it would be very
surprising if the second rejection was for the same reason as the first. At
least for the first one we were given a rejection reason; with the current
one we don't have anything right now.



Adam







On Thu, 20 May 2021 at 16:32, Millie Motteram <
Millie.Motteram@collercapital.com> wrote:

Hi Adam



Bank of New York (BNYM) have just notified us that the below wire payment,
which was initially made on 15 April 2021, has again been rejected by your
bank and returned due to a formatting error. BNYM advised that they were
able to cross reference all of the wire details provided below and the wire
was processed as standard so they are unsure why this has happened.



Please could you speak to your bank so we can establish the details
required for them to accept the wire from BNYM?



Many thanks



Millie


